forestry right”, in relation to land, means:
* an interest in the land pursuant to which a person having the benefit of the interest is
	* to establish, maintain, and harvest a crop of trees on the land;
	* to maintain and harvest a crop of trees on the land;
	* to construct and use such buildings, works and facilities as may be necessary
	* a carbon sequestration right in respect of the land; or
	* a combination of the interest and right referred to in paragraphs (a) and (b);

Until such time as the Code is in force, the Director-General may determine in writing:
* the conditions for carrying out operations, including harvesting operations, on
* harvesting plans;
* works ancillary to harvesting operations;
* soil erosion and sediment control;
* native animals and plants;
* post-harvest bush fire hazard reduction burning;
* indigenous relics and cultural or historic sites;
* the protection of unique or special animals or plants.
* does not have any effect unless it is so adopted; and
* is to be set out in the regulation that adopts it; and
* ceases to have effect if the regulation that adopts it is repealed.
